It had begun successfully in the late 1530s, according to the Rev. James MacCaffrey, writing in 1914:

Archivium Hibernicum is a peer-reviewed history journal published annually by the Catholic History Society of Ireland. It was established in 1912 and edited by Dr. James MacCaffrey Professor of Ecclesiastical History at Maynooth College, the Archivium is primarily concerned with publishing archival source material for the study of Irish history. It is Editor-in-chiefedited by Thomas O'Connor.
Monsignor Hogan resigned as president of Maynooth in October 1918 and died in Dublin on 24 November 1918. He was succeeded in Maynooth by his vice president Monsignor James MacCaffrey.
